This paper discusses the mathematical modeling of object-oriented programming, which is a topic that falls under programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper specifically focuses on the differences between nominal typing and structural typing in OOP, which relates to the topic of type theory (cs.TY). The paper also discusses inheritance and subtyping, which are topics in logic (cs.LO). Finally, the paper provides code examples to illustrate the concepts, which is a common practice in object-oriented programming (cs.OO).
